org.cpsolver.studentsct.extension

Class StudentQuality

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.cpsolver.ifs.extension.Extension<V,T>
      • org.cpsolver.ifs.assignment.context.ExtensionWithContext<Request,Enrollment,StudentQuality.StudentQualityContext>
        • org.cpsolver.studentsct.extension.StudentQuality
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CanHoldContext, CanInheritContext<Request,Enrollment,StudentQuality.StudentQualityContext>, HasAssignmentContext<Request,Enrollment,StudentQuality.StudentQualityContext>, InfoProvider<Request,Enrollment>, ModelListener<Request,Enrollment>

    public class StudentQuality
extends ExtensionWithContext<Request,Enrollment,StudentQuality.StudentQualityContext>
implements ModelListener<Request,Enrollment>, CanInheritContext<Request,Enrollment,StudentQuality.StudentQualityContext>, InfoProvider<Request,Enrollment>
    This extension computes student schedule quality using various matrices. It replaces TimeOverlapsCounter and DistanceConflict extensions. Besides of time and distance conflicts, it also counts cases when a student has a lunch break conflict, travel time during the day, it can prefer or discourage student class back-to-back and cases when a student has more than a given number of hours between the first and the last class on a day. See StudentQuality.Type for more details.

    Version:
    StudentSct 1.3 (Student Sectioning)
